{"title":"Jarod and His Bourdeau Vintage MTB Homage – John Watson","link":"https://theradavist.com/bourdeau-vintage-mtb-homage/","date":1746615617000,"content":"<p><em>Over the past two days, we’ve looked <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/amg-cyclery-shop-visit/\" target=\"_blank\">inside AMG Cyclery</a> and at the <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/beautiful-bicycles-amg-cyclery-bourdeau/\" target=\"_blank\">unique bikes on display</a> at the shop. Today, we’re featuring <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/jarodbourdeau/?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\">Jarod</a>‘s stunning Bourdeau vintage MTB homage. Read on for John’s photos of this very special <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/beautiful-bicycles/\" target=\"_blank\">Beautiful Bicycles</a> feature…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-8.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-8.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-8.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-8.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-6.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-6.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-6.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-6.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Watching the work of makers from afar via Instagram stories is perhaps one of the best things to come from social media. From the <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/chapmancycles/reels/?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\">videos of Chapman Cycles</a>, to <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/2025-bespoked-uk-day-01/#:~:text=Creature%20Cycles%20Galago%20MX%20V2%20Full%20Suspension\" target=\"_blank\">Creature Cycles’ experimentation</a> with stainless steel 3D printing, it’s one of my favorite ways to use the app. There’s something special about having the ability to connect with the global framebuilder world, all from a small device that fits in your pocket.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-30.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-30.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-30.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-30.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>One of the by-products of this connected community are the synergies that form as part of the collective ether. The bullmoose bar seems to be having a moment. From the <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/stridsland-bullship-bar-review/\" target=\"_blank\">Stridsland Bullship bars</a> to my <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/1983-ritchey-everest-restoration/\" target=\"_blank\">Ritchey restorations and deep dives</a>, I feel like there are more modern representations swirling through the small brand and maker space. As soon as I saw Jarod Bourdeau making one on his Instagram feed, I knew it was gonna be good.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-42.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-42.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-42.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-42.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-35.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-35.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-35.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-35.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-31.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-31.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-31.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-31.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Sure, there are countless details to get lost in while you examine this Bourdeau vintage MTB homage, but the jewel on the crown is the handlebar and its unique ornamentation. Tom Ritchey invented the bullmoose handlebar as we know it, and while there were French builders in the 1800s making similar constructions, Tom’s particular version has left a lasting impression in the mountain bike space. As with other bullmoose bar homages, each builder adds their unique touch. Jarod’s details include the nice bilam lugs at the tube-constructed cable hanger and integrated barrel adjuster.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-60.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-60.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-60.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-60.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-19.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-19.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-19.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-19.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-20.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-20.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-20.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-20.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Moving elsewhere on the bike, you’ll see the cable guides that run along the driveside of the top tube, like the Yetis of the ’80s. The cable hanger off the quick-release seat collar is a bent and brazed spoke. The naked steel and brass fillets aren’t raw; Jarod applied a patina from Sculpt Nouveau, a patina agent company, to give the tubes and joints a warm hue. While this doesn’t protect the steel completely, a frequent coat of lacquer will keep moisture and corrosion at bay.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-50.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-50.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-50.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-50.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-49.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-49.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-49.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-49.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-56.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-56.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-56.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-56.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>An XTR top pull derailleur and rear mech complement the White Industries VBC (variable bolt-center) cranks,  allowing for a classic, retro-mod aesthetic.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-26.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-26.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-26.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-26.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-18.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-18.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-18.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-18.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The down and top tubes are brazed into a carved head tube, which becomes a faux lug that then slides over an additional head tube, both reinforcing the bike’s front end and adding a bit of visual panache to the frame.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-666.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-666.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-666.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-666.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The bike’s intent and execution are flawless, and for being such an ostentatious endeavor, the builder himself is quite humble. My time with Spencer documenting this bike and all the bikes from AMG Cyclery was by far a highlight of our trip to the central coast of California during Sea Otter.</p>\n<p>What’s your favorite detail here? Let us know in the comments.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-1.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Bourdeau-Vintage-MTB-Homage-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Build Spec</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Frame: Bourdeau</li>\n<li>Fork: Bourdeau with Crust Crown</li>\n<li>Cranks: White Industries</li>\n<li>Front Derailleur: XTR</li>\n<li>Rear Derailleur: XTR</li>\n<li>Front Hub: SON</li>\n<li>Rear Hub: Campy Tandem</li>\n<li>Rims: Velocity</li>\n<li>Tires: Surly</li>\n<li>Cages: Velo Orange</li>\n<li>Fenders: Honjo Sim Works</li>\n<li>Seatpost: Thomson</li>\n<li>Saddle: Brooks</li>\n<li>Handlebars: Bourdeau Bullmoose</li>\n<li>Grips: ESI</li>\n<li>Shifters: Suntour</li>\n<li>Headset: Chris King</li>\n<li>Lamps: Busch &amp; Muller</li>\n<li>Bar Plugs: <a href=\"https://www.yellowbirdthreadworks.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Yellow Bird Threadworks</a></li>\n<li>Top Cap: <a href=\"https://www.yellowbirdthreadworks.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Yellow Bird Threadworks</a></li>\n<li>Brakes: IRD Cafam</li>\n<li>Cable Hanger: <a href=\"https://jubileemfg.com/heart-hanger-purchase\" target=\"_blank\">Jubilee Heart Hanger</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/bourdeau-vintage-mtb-homage/\">Jarod and His Bourdeau Vintage MTB Homage</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"3218c9c898ecd16274a3ee6f8e373ad6586f397aa382745a7a082d2f013c3b76","category":"Cycling"}